The release mechanism N, P-CDs-DOX was judged by the index of t (n) in the Ritger-Peppas equation (Q = Kpt
                           n
                        ). Data (Table S2) showed that the release mechanisms of N, P-CDs-DOX was Fick diffusion (n < 0.45) at different pH (pH = 5.0, n = 0.399; pH = 6.5, n = 0.352; pH = 7.0, n = 0.4308) (Shi et al., 2021).
